"script": "He swallowed seventy-six hot dogs in ten minutes to win the eating contest, dunking the buns in water to choke them down faster. The crowd roared as he hoisted the golden belt. But here's what nobody saw. To prepare, champions stretch their stomachs for weeks, until the organ balloons to grotesque sizes. And this trains the body to ignore the one signal that screams stop, you're full. Over time, that broken signal can stay broken, leaving them unable to feel full at all. The very skill that makes them legends slowly rewires them to never feel satisfied again.",
